3182 /// ParseAlignArgument - Parse the argument to an alignment-specifier.
3183 ///
3184 /// [C11] type-id
3185 /// [C11] constant-expression
3186 /// [C++0x] type-id ...[opt]
3187 /// [C++0x] assignment-expression ...[opt]
3188 ExprResult Parser::ParseAlignArgument(StringRef KWName, SourceLocation Start,
3189  SourceLocation &EllipsisLoc, bool &IsType,
3190  ParsedType &TypeResult) {
3191  ExprResult ER;
3192  if (isTypeIdInParens()) {
3193  SourceLocation TypeLoc = Tok.getLocation();
3194  ParsedType Ty = ParseTypeName().get();
3195  SourceRange TypeRange(Start, Tok.getLocation());
3196  if (Actions.ActOnAlignasTypeArgument(KWName, Ty, TypeLoc, TypeRange))
3197  return ExprError();
3198  TypeResult = Ty;
3199  IsType = true;
3200  } else {
3201  ER = ParseConstantExpression();
3202  IsType = false;
3203  }
3204 
3205  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
3206  TryConsumeToken(tok::ellipsis, EllipsisLoc);
3207 
3208  return ER;
3209 }

3211 /// ParseAlignmentSpecifier - Parse an alignment-specifier, and add the
3212 /// attribute to Attrs.
3213 ///
3214 /// alignment-specifier:
3215 /// [C11] '_Alignas' '(' type-id ')'
3216 /// [C11] '_Alignas' '(' constant-expression ')'
3217 /// [C++11] 'alignas' '(' type-id ...[opt] ')'
3218 /// [C++11] 'alignas' '(' assignment-expression ...[opt] ')'
3219 void Parser::ParseAlignmentSpecifier(ParsedAttributes &Attrs,
3220  SourceLocation *EndLoc) {
3221  assert(Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw_alignas, tok::kw__Alignas) &&
3222  "Not an alignment-specifier!");
3223  Token KWTok = Tok;
3224  IdentifierInfo *KWName = KWTok.getIdentifierInfo();
3225  auto Kind = KWTok.getKind();
3226  SourceLocation KWLoc = ConsumeToken();
3227 
3228  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
3229  if (T.expectAndConsume())
3230  return;
3231 
3232  bool IsType;
3233  ParsedType TypeResult;
3234  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
3235  ExprResult ArgExpr =
3236  ParseAlignArgument(PP.getSpelling(KWTok), T.getOpenLocation(),
3237  EllipsisLoc, IsType, TypeResult);
3238  if (ArgExpr.isInvalid()) {
3239  T.skipToEnd();
3240  return;
3241  }
3242 
3243  T.consumeClose();
3244  if (EndLoc)
3245  *EndLoc = T.getCloseLocation();
3246 
3247  if (IsType) {
3248  Attrs.addNewTypeAttr(KWName, KWLoc, nullptr, KWLoc, TypeResult, Kind,
3249  EllipsisLoc);
3250  } else {
3251  ArgsVector ArgExprs;
3252  ArgExprs.push_back(ArgExpr.get());
3253  Attrs.addNew(KWName, KWLoc, nullptr, KWLoc, ArgExprs.data(), 1, Kind,
3254  EllipsisLoc);
3255  }
3256 }

3258 /// Bounds attributes (e.g., counted_by):
3259 /// AttrName '(' expression ')'
3260 void Parser::ParseBoundsAttribute(IdentifierInfo &AttrName,
3261  SourceLocation AttrNameLoc,
3262  ParsedAttributes &Attrs,
3263  IdentifierInfo *ScopeName,
3264  SourceLocation ScopeLoc,
3265  ParsedAttr::Form Form) {
3266  assert(Tok.is(tok::l_paren) && "Attribute arg list not starting with '('");
3267 
3268  BalancedDelimiterTracker Parens(*this, tok::l_paren);
3269  Parens.consumeOpen();
3270 
3271  if (Tok.is(tok::r_paren)) {
3272  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_argument_required_after_attribute);
3273  Parens.consumeClose();
3274  return;
3275  }
3276 
3277  ArgsVector ArgExprs;
3278  // Don't evaluate argument when the attribute is ignored.
3279  using ExpressionKind =
3280  Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::ExpressionKind;
3281  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext EC(
3282  Actions, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated, nullptr,
3283  ExpressionKind::EK_BoundsAttrArgument);
3284 
3285  ExprResult ArgExpr(
3286  Actions.CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(ParseAssignmentExpression()));
3287 
3288  if (ArgExpr.isInvalid()) {
3289  Parens.skipToEnd();
3290  return;
3291  }
3292 
3293  ArgExprs.push_back(ArgExpr.get());
3294  Parens.consumeClose();
3295 
3296  ASTContext &Ctx = Actions.getASTContext();
3297 
3298  ArgExprs.push_back(IntegerLiteral::Create(
3299  Ctx, llvm::APInt(Ctx.getTypeSize(Ctx.getSizeType()), 0),
3300  Ctx.getSizeType(), SourceLocation()));
3301 
3302  Attrs.addNew(&AttrName, SourceRange(AttrNameLoc, Parens.getCloseLocation()),
3303  ScopeName, ScopeLoc, ArgExprs.data(), ArgExprs.size(), Form);
3304 }

3306 ExprResult Parser::ParseExtIntegerArgument() {

3326 /// Determine whether we're looking at something that might be a declarator
3327 /// in a simple-declaration. If it can't possibly be a declarator, maybe
3328 /// diagnose a missing semicolon after a prior tag definition in the decl
3329 /// specifier.
3330 ///
3331 /// \return \c true if an error occurred and this can't be any kind of
3332 /// declaration.
3333 bool
3334 Parser::DiagnoseMissingSemiAfterTagDefinition(DeclSpec &DS, AccessSpecifier AS,
3335  DeclSpecContext DSContext,
3336  LateParsedAttrList *LateAttrs) {
3337  assert(DS.hasTagDefinition() && "shouldn't call this");
3338 
3339  bool EnteringContext = (DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class ||
3340  DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_top_level);
3341 
3342  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
3343  Tok.isOneOf(tok::identifier, tok::coloncolon, tok::kw_decltype,
3344  tok::annot_template_id) &&
3345  TryAnnotateCXXScopeToken(EnteringContext)) {
3346  SkipMalformedDecl();
3347  return true;
3348  }
3349 
3350  bool HasScope = Tok.is(tok::annot_cxxscope);
3351  // Make a copy in case GetLookAheadToken invalidates the result of NextToken.
3352  Token AfterScope = HasScope ? NextToken() : Tok;
3353 
3354  // Determine whether the following tokens could possibly be a
3355  // declarator.
3356  bool MightBeDeclarator = true;
3357  if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw_typename, tok::annot_typename)) {
3358  // A declarator-id can't start with 'typename'.
3359  MightBeDeclarator = false;
3360  } else if (AfterScope.is(tok::annot_template_id)) {
3361  // If we have a type expressed as a template-id, this cannot be a
3362  // declarator-id (such a type cannot be redeclared in a simple-declaration).
3363  TemplateIdAnnotation *Annot =
3364  static_cast<TemplateIdAnnotation *>(AfterScope.getAnnotationValue());
3365  if (Annot->Kind == TNK_Type_template)
3366  MightBeDeclarator = false;
3367  } else if (AfterScope.is(tok::identifier)) {
3368  const Token &Next = HasScope ? GetLookAheadToken(2) : NextToken();
3369 
3370  // These tokens cannot come after the declarator-id in a
3371  // simple-declaration, and are likely to come after a type-specifier.
3372  if (Next.isOneOf(tok::star, tok::amp, tok::ampamp, tok::identifier,
3373  tok::annot_cxxscope, tok::coloncolon)) {
3374  // Missing a semicolon.
3375  MightBeDeclarator = false;
3376  } else if (HasScope) {
3377  // If the declarator-id has a scope specifier, it must redeclare a
3378  // previously-declared entity. If that's a type (and this is not a
3379  // typedef), that's an error.
3380  CXXScopeSpec SS;
3381  Actions.RestoreNestedNameSpecifierAnnotation(
3382  Tok.getAnnotationValue(), Tok.getAnnotationRange(), SS);
3383  IdentifierInfo *Name = AfterScope.getIdentifierInfo();
3384  Sema::NameClassification Classification = Actions.ClassifyName(
3385  getCurScope(), SS, Name, AfterScope.getLocation(), Next,
3386  /*CCC=*/nullptr);
3387  switch (Classification.getKind()) {
3388  case Sema::NC_Error:
3389  SkipMalformedDecl();
3390  return true;
3391 
3392  case Sema::NC_Keyword:
3393  llvm_unreachable("typo correction is not possible here");
3394 
3395  case Sema::NC_Type:
3396  case Sema::NC_TypeTemplate:
3397  case Sema::NC_UndeclaredNonType:
3398  case Sema::NC_UndeclaredTemplate:
3399  // Not a previously-declared non-type entity.
3400  MightBeDeclarator = false;
3401  break;
3402 
3403  case Sema::NC_Unknown:
3404  case Sema::NC_NonType:
3405  case Sema::NC_DependentNonType:
3406  case Sema::NC_OverloadSet:
3407  case Sema::NC_VarTemplate:
3408  case Sema::NC_FunctionTemplate:
3409  case Sema::NC_Concept:
3410  // Might be a redeclaration of a prior entity.
3411  break;
3412  }
3413  }
3414  }
3415 
3416  if (MightBeDeclarator)
3417  return false;
3418 
3419  const PrintingPolicy &PPol = Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy();
3420  Diag(PP.getLocForEndOfToken(DS.getRepAsDecl()->getEndLoc()),
3421  diag::err_expected_after)
3422  << DeclSpec::getSpecifierName(DS.getTypeSpecType(), PPol) << tok::semi;
3423 
3424  // Try to recover from the typo, by dropping the tag definition and parsing
3425  // the problematic tokens as a type.
3426  //
3427  // FIXME: Split the DeclSpec into pieces for the standalone
3428  // declaration and pieces for the following declaration, instead
3429  // of assuming that all the other pieces attach to new declaration,
3430  // and call ParsedFreeStandingDeclSpec as appropriate.
3431  DS.ClearTypeSpecType();
3432  ParsedTemplateInfo NotATemplate;
3433  ParseDeclarationSpecifiers(DS, NotATemplate, AS, DSContext, LateAttrs);
3434  return false;
3435 }
3436 
3437 /// ParseDeclarationSpecifiers
3438 /// declaration-specifiers: [C99 6.7]
3439 /// storage-class-specifier declaration-specifiers[opt]
3440 /// type-specifier declaration-specifiers[opt]
3441 /// [C99] function-specifier declaration-specifiers[opt]
3442 /// [C11] alignment-specifier declaration-specifiers[opt]
3443 /// [GNU] attributes declaration-specifiers[opt]
3444 /// [Clang] '__module_private__' declaration-specifiers[opt]
3445 /// [ObjC1] '__kindof' declaration-specifiers[opt]
3446 ///
3447 /// storage-class-specifier: [C99 6.7.1]
3448 /// 'typedef'
3449 /// 'extern'
3450 /// 'static'
3451 /// 'auto'
3452 /// 'register'
3453 /// [C++] 'mutable'
3454 /// [C++11] 'thread_local'
3455 /// [C11] '_Thread_local'
3456 /// [GNU] '__thread'
3457 /// function-specifier: [C99 6.7.4]
3458 /// [C99] 'inline'
3459 /// [C++] 'virtual'
3460 /// [C++] 'explicit'
3461 /// [OpenCL] '__kernel'
3462 /// 'friend': [C++ dcl.friend]
3463 /// 'constexpr': [C++0x dcl.constexpr]
3464 void Parser::ParseDeclarationSpecifiers(
3465  DeclSpec &DS, const ParsedTemplateInfo &TemplateInfo, AccessSpecifier AS,
3466  DeclSpecContext DSContext, LateParsedAttrList *LateAttrs,
3467  ImplicitTypenameContext AllowImplicitTypename) {
3468  if (DS.getSourceRange().isInvalid()) {
3469  // Start the range at the current token but make the end of the range
3470  // invalid. This will make the entire range invalid unless we successfully
3471  // consume a token.
3472  DS.SetRangeStart(Tok.getLocation());
3473  DS.SetRangeEnd(SourceLocation());
3474  }
3475 
3476  // If we are in a operator context, convert it back into a type specifier
3477  // context for better error handling later on.
3478  if (DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_conv_operator) {
3479  // No implicit typename here.
3480  AllowImplicitTypename = ImplicitTypenameContext::No;
3481  DSContext = DeclSpecContext::DSC_type_specifier;
3482  }
3483 
3484  bool EnteringContext = (DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class ||
3485  DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_top_level);
3486  bool AttrsLastTime = false;
3487  ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
3488  // We use Sema's policy to get bool macros right.
3489  PrintingPolicy Policy = Actions.getPrintingPolicy();
3490  while (true) {
3491  bool isInvalid = false;
3492  bool isStorageClass = false;
3493  const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
3494  unsigned DiagID = 0;
3495 
3496  // This value needs to be set to the location of the last token if the last
3497  // token of the specifier is already consumed.
3498  SourceLocation ConsumedEnd;
3499 
3500  // HACK: MSVC doesn't consider _Atomic to be a keyword and its STL
3501  // implementation for VS2013 uses _Atomic as an identifier for one of the
3502  // classes in <atomic>.
3503  //
3504  // A typedef declaration containing _Atomic<...> is among the places where
3505  // the class is used. If we are currently parsing such a declaration, treat
3506  // the token as an identifier.
3507  if (getLangOpts().MSVCCompat && Tok.is(tok::kw__Atomic) &&
3508  DS.getStorageClassSpec() == clang::DeclSpec::SCS_typedef &&
3509  !DS.hasTypeSpecifier() && GetLookAheadToken(1).is(tok::less))
3510  Tok.setKind(tok::identifier);
3511 
3512  SourceLocation Loc = Tok.getLocation();
3513 
3514  // Helper for image types in OpenCL.
3515  auto handleOpenCLImageKW = [&] (StringRef Ext, TypeSpecifierType ImageTypeSpec) {
3516  // Check if the image type is supported and otherwise turn the keyword into an identifier
3517  // because image types from extensions are not reserved identifiers.
3518  if (!StringRef(Ext).empty() && !getActions().getOpenCLOptions().isSupported(Ext, getLangOpts())) {
3519  Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->revertTokenIDToIdentifier();
3520  Tok.setKind(tok::identifier);
3521  return false;
3522  }
3523  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(ImageTypeSpec, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
3524  return true;
3525  };
3526 
3527  // Turn off usual access checking for template specializations and
3528  // instantiations.
3529  bool IsTemplateSpecOrInst =
3530  (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitInstantiation ||
3531  TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitSpecialization);
3532 
3533  switch (Tok.getKind()) {
3534  default:
3535  if (Tok.isRegularKeywordAttribute())
3536  goto Attribute;
3537 
3538  DoneWithDeclSpec:
3539  if (!AttrsLastTime)
3540  ProhibitAttributes(attrs);
3541  else {
3542  // Reject C++11 / C23 attributes that aren't type attributes.
3543  for (const ParsedAttr &PA : attrs) {
3544  if (!PA.isCXX11Attribute() && !PA.isC23Attribute() &&
3545  !PA.isRegularKeywordAttribute())
3546  continue;
3547  if (PA.getKind() == ParsedAttr::UnknownAttribute)
3548  // We will warn about the unknown attribute elsewhere (in
3549  // SemaDeclAttr.cpp)
3550  continue;
3551  // GCC ignores this attribute when placed on the DeclSpec in [[]]
3552  // syntax, so we do the same.
3553  if (PA.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_VectorSize) {
3554  Diag(PA.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << PA;
3555  PA.setInvalid();
3556  continue;
3557  }
3558  // We reject AT_LifetimeBound and AT_AnyX86NoCfCheck, even though they
3559  // are type attributes, because we historically haven't allowed these
3560  // to be used as type attributes in C++11 / C23 syntax.
3561  if (PA.isTypeAttr() && PA.getKind() != ParsedAttr::AT_LifetimeBound &&
3562  PA.getKind() != ParsedAttr::AT_AnyX86NoCfCheck)
3563  continue;
3564  Diag(PA.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_not_type_attr)
3565  << PA << PA.isRegularKeywordAttribute();
3566  PA.setInvalid();
3567  }
3568 
3569  DS.takeAttributesFrom(attrs);
3570  }
3571 
3572  // If this is not a declaration specifier token, we're done reading decl
3573  // specifiers. First verify that DeclSpec's are consistent.
3574  DS.Finish(Actions, Policy);
3575  return;
3576 
3577  // alignment-specifier
3578  case tok::kw__Alignas:
3579  diagnoseUseOfC11Keyword(Tok);
3580  [[fallthrough]];
3581  case tok::kw_alignas:
3582  // _Alignas and alignas (C23, not C++) should parse the same way. The C++
3583  // parsing for alignas happens through the usual attribute parsing. This
3584  // ensures that an alignas specifier can appear in a type position in C
3585  // despite that not being valid in C++.
3586  if (getLangOpts().C23 || Tok.getKind() == tok::kw__Alignas) {
3587  if (Tok.getKind() == tok::kw_alignas)
3588  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_c23_compat_keyword) << Tok.getName();
3589  ParseAlignmentSpecifier(DS.getAttributes());
3590  continue;
3591  }
3592  [[fallthrough]];
3593  case tok::l_square:
3594  if (!isAllowedCXX11AttributeSpecifier())
3595  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3596 
3597  Attribute:
3598  ProhibitAttributes(attrs);
3599  // FIXME: It would be good to recover by accepting the attributes,
3600  // but attempting to do that now would cause serious
3601  // madness in terms of diagnostics.
3602  attrs.clear();
3603  attrs.Range = SourceRange();
3604 
3605  ParseCXX11Attributes(attrs);
3606  AttrsLastTime = true;
3607  continue;
3608 
3609  case tok::code_completion: {
3610  Sema::ParserCompletionContext CCC = Sema::PCC_Namespace;
3611  if (DS.hasTypeSpecifier()) {
3612  bool AllowNonIdentifiers
3613  = (getCurScope()->getFlags() & (Scope::ControlScope |
3614  Scope::BlockScope |
3615  Scope::TemplateParamScope |
3616  Scope::FunctionPrototypeScope |
3617  Scope::AtCatchScope)) == 0;
3618  bool AllowNestedNameSpecifiers
3619  = DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_top_level ||
3620  (DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class && DS.isFriendSpecified());
3621 
3622  cutOffParsing();
3623  Actions.CodeCompleteDeclSpec(getCurScope(), DS,
3624  AllowNonIdentifiers,
3625  AllowNestedNameSpecifiers);
3626  return;
3627  }
3628 
3629  // Class context can appear inside a function/block, so prioritise that.
3630  if (TemplateInfo.Kind != ParsedTemplateInfo::NonTemplate)
3631  CCC = DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class ? Sema::PCC_MemberTemplate
3632  : Sema::PCC_Template;
3633  else if (DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class)
3634  CCC = Sema::PCC_Class;
3635  else if (getCurScope()->getFnParent() || getCurScope()->getBlockParent())
3636  CCC = Sema::PCC_LocalDeclarationSpecifiers;
3637  else if (CurParsedObjCImpl)
3638  CCC = Sema::PCC_ObjCImplementation;
3639 
3640  cutOffParsing();
3641  Actions.CodeCompleteOrdinaryName(getCurScope(), CCC);
3642  return;
3643  }
3644 
3645  case tok::coloncolon: // ::foo::bar
3646  // C++ scope specifier. Annotate and loop, or bail out on error.
3647  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
3648  TryAnnotateCXXScopeToken(EnteringContext)) {
3649  if (!DS.hasTypeSpecifier())
3650  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
3651  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3652  }
3653  if (Tok.is(tok::coloncolon)) // ::new or ::delete
3654  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3655  continue;
3656 
3657  case tok::annot_cxxscope: {
3658  if (DS.hasTypeSpecifier() || DS.isTypeAltiVecVector())
3659  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3660 
3661  CXXScopeSpec SS;
3662  if (TemplateInfo.TemplateParams)
3663  SS.setTemplateParamLists(*TemplateInfo.TemplateParams);
3664  Actions.RestoreNestedNameSpecifierAnnotation(Tok.getAnnotationValue(),
3665  Tok.getAnnotationRange(),
3666  SS);
3667 
3668  // We are looking for a qualified typename.
3669  Token Next = NextToken();
3670 
3671  TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = Next.is(tok::annot_template_id)
3672  ? takeTemplateIdAnnotation(Next)
3673  : nullptr;
3674  if (TemplateId && TemplateId->hasInvalidName()) {
3675  // We found something like 'T::U<Args> x', but U is not a template.
3676  // Assume it was supposed to be a type.
3677  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
3678  ConsumeAnnotationToken();
3679  break;
3680  }
3681 
3682  if (TemplateId && TemplateId->Kind == TNK_Type_template) {
3683  // We have a qualified template-id, e.g., N::A<int>
3684 
3685  // If this would be a valid constructor declaration with template
3686  // arguments, we will reject the attempt to form an invalid type-id
3687  // referring to the injected-class-name when we annotate the token,
3688  // per C++ [class.qual]p2.
3689  //
3690  // To improve diagnostics for this case, parse the declaration as a
3691  // constructor (and reject the extra template arguments later).
3692  if ((DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_top_level ||
3693  DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class) &&
3694  TemplateId->Name &&
3695  Actions.isCurrentClassName(*TemplateId->Name, getCurScope(), &SS) &&
3696  isConstructorDeclarator(/*Unqualified=*/false,
3697  /*DeductionGuide=*/false,
3698  DS.isFriendSpecified())) {
3699  // The user meant this to be an out-of-line constructor
3700  // definition, but template arguments are not allowed
3701  // there. Just allow this as a constructor; we'll
3702  // complain about it later.
3703  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3704  }
3705 
3706  DS.getTypeSpecScope() = SS;
3707  ConsumeAnnotationToken(); // The C++ scope.
3708  assert(Tok.is(tok::annot_template_id) &&
3709  "ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier not working");
3710  AnnotateTemplateIdTokenAsType(SS, AllowImplicitTypename);
3711  continue;
3712  }
3713 
3714  if (TemplateId && TemplateId->Kind == TNK_Concept_template) {
3715  DS.getTypeSpecScope() = SS;
3716  // This is probably a qualified placeholder-specifier, e.g., ::C<int>
3717  // auto ... Consume the scope annotation and continue to consume the
3718  // template-id as a placeholder-specifier. Let the next iteration
3719  // diagnose a missing auto.
3720  ConsumeAnnotationToken();
3721  continue;
3722  }
3723 
3724  if (Next.is(tok::annot_typename)) {
3725  DS.getTypeSpecScope() = SS;
3726  ConsumeAnnotationToken(); // The C++ scope.
3727  TypeResult T = getTypeAnnotation(Tok);
3728  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_typename,
3729  Tok.getAnnotationEndLoc(),
3730  PrevSpec, DiagID, T, Policy);
3731  if (isInvalid)
3732  break;
3733  DS.SetRangeEnd(Tok.getAnnotationEndLoc());
3734  ConsumeAnnotationToken(); // The typename
3735  }
3736 
3737  if (AllowImplicitTypename == ImplicitTypenameContext::Yes &&
3738  Next.is(tok::annot_template_id) &&
3739  static_cast<TemplateIdAnnotation *>(Next.getAnnotationValue())
3740  ->Kind == TNK_Dependent_template_name) {
3741  DS.getTypeSpecScope() = SS;
3742  ConsumeAnnotationToken(); // The C++ scope.
3743  AnnotateTemplateIdTokenAsType(SS, AllowImplicitTypename);
3744  continue;
3745  }
3746 
3747  if (Next.isNot(tok::identifier))
3748  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3749 
3750  // Check whether this is a constructor declaration. If we're in a
3751  // context where the identifier could be a class name, and it has the
3752  // shape of a constructor declaration, process it as one.
3753  if ((DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_top_level ||
3754  DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class) &&
3755  Actions.isCurrentClassName(*Next.getIdentifierInfo(), getCurScope(),
3756  &SS) &&
3757  isConstructorDeclarator(/*Unqualified=*/false,
3758  /*DeductionGuide=*/false,
3759  DS.isFriendSpecified(),
3760  &TemplateInfo))
3761  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3762 
3763  // C++20 [temp.spec] 13.9/6.
3764  // This disables the access checking rules for function template explicit
3765  // instantiation and explicit specialization:
3766  // - `return type`.
3767  SuppressAccessChecks SAC(*this, IsTemplateSpecOrInst);
3768 
3769  ParsedType TypeRep = Actions.getTypeName(
3770  *Next.getIdentifierInfo(), Next.getLocation(), getCurScope(), &SS,
3771  false, false, nullptr,
3772  /*IsCtorOrDtorName=*/false,
3773  /*WantNontrivialTypeSourceInfo=*/true,
3774  isClassTemplateDeductionContext(DSContext), AllowImplicitTypename);
3775 
3776  if (IsTemplateSpecOrInst)
3777  SAC.done();
3778 
3779  // If the referenced identifier is not a type, then this declspec is
3780  // erroneous: We already checked about that it has no type specifier, and
3781  // C++ doesn't have implicit int. Diagnose it as a typo w.r.t. to the
3782  // typename.
3783  if (!TypeRep) {
3784  if (TryAnnotateTypeConstraint())
3785  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3786  if (Tok.isNot(tok::annot_cxxscope) ||
3787  NextToken().isNot(tok::identifier))
3788  continue;
3789  // Eat the scope spec so the identifier is current.
3790  ConsumeAnnotationToken();
3791  ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
3792  if (ParseImplicitInt(DS, &SS, TemplateInfo, AS, DSContext, Attrs)) {
3793  if (!Attrs.empty()) {
3794  AttrsLastTime = true;
3795  attrs.takeAllFrom(Attrs);
3796  }
3797  continue;
3798  }
3799  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3800  }
3801 
3802  DS.getTypeSpecScope() = SS;
3803  ConsumeAnnotationToken(); // The C++ scope.
3804 
3805  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_typename, Loc, PrevSpec,
3806  DiagID, TypeRep, Policy);
3807  if (isInvalid)
3808  break;
3809 
3810  DS.SetRangeEnd(Tok.getLocation());
3811  ConsumeToken(); // The typename.
3812 
3813  continue;
3814  }
3815 
3816  case tok::annot_typename: {
3817  // If we've previously seen a tag definition, we were almost surely
3818  // missing a semicolon after it.
3819  if (DS.hasTypeSpecifier() && DS.hasTagDefinition())
3820  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3821 
3822  TypeResult T = getTypeAnnotation(Tok);
3823  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_typename, Loc, PrevSpec,
3824  DiagID, T, Policy);
3825  if (isInvalid)
3826  break;
3827 
3828  DS.SetRangeEnd(Tok.getAnnotationEndLoc());
3829  ConsumeAnnotationToken(); // The typename
3830 
3831  continue;
3832  }
3833 
3834  case tok::kw___is_signed:
3835  // GNU libstdc++ 4.4 uses __is_signed as an identifier, but Clang
3836  // typically treats it as a trait. If we see __is_signed as it appears
3837  // in libstdc++, e.g.,
3838  //
3839  // static const bool __is_signed;
3840  //
3841  // then treat __is_signed as an identifier rather than as a keyword.
3842  if (DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_bool &&
3843  DS.getTypeQualifiers() == DeclSpec::TQ_const &&
3844  DS.getStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::SCS_static)
3845  TryKeywordIdentFallback(true);
3846 
3847  // We're done with the declaration-specifiers.
3848  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3849 
3850  // typedef-name
3851  case tok::kw___super:
3852  case tok::kw_decltype:
3853  case tok::identifier:
3854  ParseIdentifier: {
3855  // This identifier can only be a typedef name if we haven't already seen
3856  // a type-specifier. Without this check we misparse:
3857  // typedef int X; struct Y { short X; }; as 'short int'.
3858  if (DS.hasTypeSpecifier())
3859  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3860 
3861  // If the token is an identifier named "__declspec" and Microsoft
3862  // extensions are not enabled, it is likely that there will be cascading
3863  // parse errors if this really is a __declspec attribute. Attempt to
3864  // recognize that scenario and recover gracefully.
3865  if (!getLangOpts().DeclSpecKeyword && Tok.is(tok::identifier) &&
3866  Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getName().equals("__declspec")) {
3867  Diag(Loc, diag::err_ms_attributes_not_enabled);
3868 
3869  // The next token should be an open paren. If it is, eat the entire
3870  // attribute declaration and continue.
3871  if (NextToken().is(tok::l_paren)) {
3872  // Consume the __declspec identifier.
3873  ConsumeToken();
3874 
3875  // Eat the parens and everything between them.
3876  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
3877  if (T.consumeOpen()) {
3878  assert(false && "Not a left paren?");
3879  return;
3880  }
3881  T.skipToEnd();
3882  continue;
3883  }
3884  }
3885 
3886  // In C++, check to see if this is a scope specifier like foo::bar::, if
3887  // so handle it as such. This is important for ctor parsing.
3888  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
3889  // C++20 [temp.spec] 13.9/6.
3890  // This disables the access checking rules for function template
3891  // explicit instantiation and explicit specialization:
3892  // - `return type`.
3893  SuppressAccessChecks SAC(*this, IsTemplateSpecOrInst);
3894 
3895  const bool Success = TryAnnotateCXXScopeToken(EnteringContext);
3896 
3897  if (IsTemplateSpecOrInst)
3898  SAC.done();
3899 
3900  if (Success) {
3901  if (IsTemplateSpecOrInst)
3902  SAC.redelay();
3903  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
3904  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3905  }
3906 
3907  if (!Tok.is(tok::identifier))
3908  continue;
3909  }
3910 
3911  // Check for need to substitute AltiVec keyword tokens.
3912  if (TryAltiVecToken(DS, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, isInvalid))
3913  break;
3914 
3915  // [AltiVec] 2.2: [If the 'vector' specifier is used] The syntax does not
3916  // allow the use of a typedef name as a type specifier.
3917  if (DS.isTypeAltiVecVector())
3918  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3919 
3920  if (DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_objc_method_result &&
3921  isObjCInstancetype()) {
3922  ParsedType TypeRep = Actions.ActOnObjCInstanceType(Loc);
3923  assert(TypeRep);
3924  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_typename, Loc, PrevSpec,
3925  DiagID, TypeRep, Policy);
3926  if (isInvalid)
3927  break;
3928 
3929  DS.SetRangeEnd(Loc);
3930  ConsumeToken();
3931  continue;
3932  }
3933 
3934  // If we're in a context where the identifier could be a class name,
3935  // check whether this is a constructor declaration.
3936  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class &&
3937  Actions.isCurrentClassName(*Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), getCurScope()) &&
3938  isConstructorDeclarator(/*Unqualified=*/true,
3939  /*DeductionGuide=*/false,
3940  DS.isFriendSpecified()))
3941  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3942 
3943  ParsedType TypeRep = Actions.getTypeName(
3944  *Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), Tok.getLocation(), getCurScope(), nullptr,
3945  false, false, nullptr, false, false,
3946  isClassTemplateDeductionContext(DSContext));
3947 
3948  // If this is not a typedef name, don't parse it as part of the declspec,
3949  // it must be an implicit int or an error.
3950  if (!TypeRep) {
3951  if (TryAnnotateTypeConstraint())
3952  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3953  if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier))
3954  continue;
3955  ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
3956  if (ParseImplicitInt(DS, nullptr, TemplateInfo, AS, DSContext, Attrs)) {
3957  if (!Attrs.empty()) {
3958  AttrsLastTime = true;
3959  attrs.takeAllFrom(Attrs);
3960  }
3961  continue;
3962  }
3963  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3964  }
3965 
3966  // Likewise, if this is a context where the identifier could be a template
3967  // name, check whether this is a deduction guide declaration.
3968  CXXScopeSpec SS;
3969  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 &&
3970  (DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class ||
3971  DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_top_level) &&
3972  Actions.isDeductionGuideName(getCurScope(), *Tok.getIdentifierInfo(),
3973  Tok.getLocation(), SS) &&
3974  isConstructorDeclarator(/*Unqualified*/ true,
3975  /*DeductionGuide*/ true))
3976  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
3977 
3978  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_typename, Loc, PrevSpec,
3979  DiagID, TypeRep, Policy);
3980  if (isInvalid)
3981  break;
3982 
3983  DS.SetRangeEnd(Tok.getLocation());
3984  ConsumeToken(); // The identifier
3985 
3986  // Objective-C supports type arguments and protocol references
3987  // following an Objective-C object or object pointer
3988  // type. Handle either one of them.
3989  if (Tok.is(tok::less) && getLangOpts().ObjC) {
3990  SourceLocation NewEndLoc;
3991  TypeResult NewTypeRep = parseObjCTypeArgsAndProtocolQualifiers(
3992  Loc, TypeRep, /*consumeLastToken=*/true,
3993  NewEndLoc);
3994  if (NewTypeRep.isUsable()) {
3995  DS.UpdateTypeRep(NewTypeRep.get());
3996  DS.SetRangeEnd(NewEndLoc);
3997  }
3998  }
3999 
4000  // Need to support trailing type qualifiers (e.g. "id<p> const").
4001  // If a type specifier follows, it will be diagnosed elsewhere.
4002  continue;
4003  }
4004 
4005  // type-name or placeholder-specifier
4006  case tok::annot_template_id: {
4007  TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = takeTemplateIdAnnotation(Tok);
4008 
4009  if (TemplateId->hasInvalidName()) {
4010  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
4011  break;
4012  }
4013 
4014  if (TemplateId->Kind == TNK_Concept_template) {
4015  // If we've already diagnosed that this type-constraint has invalid
4016  // arguments, drop it and just form 'auto' or 'decltype(auto)'.
4017  if (TemplateId->hasInvalidArgs())
4018  TemplateId = nullptr;
4019 
4020  // Any of the following tokens are likely the start of the user
4021  // forgetting 'auto' or 'decltype(auto)', so diagnose.
4022  // Note: if updating this list, please make sure we update
4023  // isCXXDeclarationSpecifier's check for IsPlaceholderSpecifier to have
4024  // a matching list.
4025  if (NextToken().isOneOf(tok::identifier, tok::kw_const,
4026  tok::kw_volatile, tok::kw_restrict, tok::amp,
4027  tok::ampamp)) {
4028  Diag(Loc, diag::err_placeholder_expected_auto_or_decltype_auto)
4029  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(NextToken().getLocation(), "auto");
4030  // Attempt to continue as if 'auto' was placed here.
4031  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(TST_auto, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4032  TemplateId, Policy);
4033  break;
4034  }
4035  if (!NextToken().isOneOf(tok::kw_auto, tok::kw_decltype))
4036  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
4037 
4038  if (TemplateId && !isInvalid && Actions.CheckTypeConstraint(TemplateId))
4039  TemplateId = nullptr;
4040 
4041  ConsumeAnnotationToken();
4042  SourceLocation AutoLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4043  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::kw_decltype)) {
4044  BalancedDelimiterTracker Tracker(*this, tok::l_paren);
4045  if (Tracker.consumeOpen()) {
4046  // Something like `void foo(Iterator decltype i)`
4047  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::l_paren;
4048  } else {
4049  if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::kw_auto)) {
4050  // Something like `void foo(Iterator decltype(int) i)`
4051  Tracker.skipToEnd();
4052  Diag(Tok, diag::err_placeholder_expected_auto_or_decltype_auto)
4053  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(SourceRange(AutoLoc,
4054  Tok.getLocation()),
4055  "auto");
4056  } else {
4057  Tracker.consumeClose();
4058  }
4059  }
4060  ConsumedEnd = Tok.getLocation();
4061  DS.setTypeArgumentRange(Tracker.getRange());
4062  // Even if something went wrong above, continue as if we've seen
4063  // `decltype(auto)`.
4064  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(TST_decltype_auto, Loc, PrevSpec,
4065  DiagID, TemplateId, Policy);
4066  } else {
4067  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(TST_auto, AutoLoc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4068  TemplateId, Policy);
4069  }
4070  break;
4071  }
4072 
4073  if (TemplateId->Kind != TNK_Type_template &&
4074  TemplateId->Kind != TNK_Undeclared_template) {
4075  // This template-id does not refer to a type name, so we're
4076  // done with the type-specifiers.
4077  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
4078  }
4079 
4080  // If we're in a context where the template-id could be a
4081  // constructor name or specialization, check whether this is a
4082  // constructor declaration.
4083  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class &&
4084  Actions.isCurrentClassName(*TemplateId->Name, getCurScope()) &&
4085  isConstructorDeclarator(/*Unqualified=*/true,
4086  /*DeductionGuide=*/false,
4087  DS.isFriendSpecified()))
4088  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
4089 
4090  // Turn the template-id annotation token into a type annotation
4091  // token, then try again to parse it as a type-specifier.
4092  CXXScopeSpec SS;
4093  AnnotateTemplateIdTokenAsType(SS, AllowImplicitTypename);
4094  continue;
4095  }
4096 
4097  // Attributes support.
4098  case tok::kw___attribute:
4099  case tok::kw___declspec:
4100  ParseAttributes(PAKM_GNU | PAKM_Declspec, DS.getAttributes(), LateAttrs);
4101  continue;
4102 
4103  // Microsoft single token adornments.
4104  case tok::kw___forceinline: {
4105  isInvalid = DS.setFunctionSpecForceInline(Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4106  IdentifierInfo *AttrName = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
4107  SourceLocation AttrNameLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4108  DS.getAttributes().addNew(AttrName, AttrNameLoc, nullptr, AttrNameLoc,
4109  nullptr, 0, tok::kw___forceinline);
4110  break;
4111  }
4112 
4113  case tok::kw___unaligned:
4114  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_unaligned, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4115  getLangOpts());
4116  break;
4117 
4118  case tok::kw___sptr:
4119  case tok::kw___uptr:
4120  case tok::kw___ptr64:
4121  case tok::kw___ptr32:
4122  case tok::kw___w64:
4123  case tok::kw___cdecl:
4124  case tok::kw___stdcall:
4125  case tok::kw___fastcall:
4126  case tok::kw___thiscall:
4127  case tok::kw___regcall:
4128  case tok::kw___vectorcall:
4129  ParseMicrosoftTypeAttributes(DS.getAttributes());
4130  continue;
4131 
4132  case tok::kw___funcref:
4133  ParseWebAssemblyFuncrefTypeAttribute(DS.getAttributes());
4134  continue;
4135 
4136  // Borland single token adornments.
4137  case tok::kw___pascal:
4138  ParseBorlandTypeAttributes(DS.getAttributes());
4139  continue;
4140 
4141  // OpenCL single token adornments.
4142  case tok::kw___kernel:
4143  ParseOpenCLKernelAttributes(DS.getAttributes());
4144  continue;
4145 
4146  // CUDA/HIP single token adornments.
4147  case tok::kw___noinline__:
4148  ParseCUDAFunctionAttributes(DS.getAttributes());
4149  continue;
4150 
4151  // Nullability type specifiers.
4152  case tok::kw__Nonnull:
4153  case tok::kw__Nullable:
4154  case tok::kw__Nullable_result:
4155  case tok::kw__Null_unspecified:
4156  ParseNullabilityTypeSpecifiers(DS.getAttributes());
4157  continue;
4158 
4159  // Objective-C 'kindof' types.
4160  case tok::kw___kindof:
4161  DS.getAttributes().addNew(Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), Loc, nullptr, Loc,
4162  nullptr, 0, tok::kw___kindof);
4163  (void)ConsumeToken();
4164  continue;
4165 
4166  // storage-class-specifier
4167  case tok::kw_typedef:
4168  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpec(Actions, DeclSpec::SCS_typedef, Loc,
4169  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4170  isStorageClass = true;
4171  break;
4172  case tok::kw_extern:
4173  if (DS.getThreadStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::TSCS___thread)
4174  Diag(Tok, diag::ext_thread_before) << "extern";
4175  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpec(Actions, DeclSpec::SCS_extern, Loc,
4176  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4177  isStorageClass = true;
4178  break;
4179  case tok::kw___private_extern__:
4180  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpec(Actions, DeclSpec::SCS_private_extern,
4181  Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4182  isStorageClass = true;
4183  break;
4184  case tok::kw_static:
4185  if (DS.getThreadStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::TSCS___thread)
4186  Diag(Tok, diag::ext_thread_before) << "static";
4187  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpec(Actions, DeclSpec::SCS_static, Loc,
4188  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4189  isStorageClass = true;
4190  break;
4191  case tok::kw_auto:
4192  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 || getLangOpts().C23) {
4193  if (isKnownToBeTypeSpecifier(GetLookAheadToken(1))) {
4194  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpec(Actions, DeclSpec::SCS_auto, Loc,
4195  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4196  if (!isInvalid && !getLangOpts().C23)
4197  Diag(Tok, diag::ext_auto_storage_class)
4198  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(DS.getStorageClassSpecLoc());
4199  } else
4200  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_auto, Loc, PrevSpec,
4201  DiagID, Policy);
4202  } else
4203  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpec(Actions, DeclSpec::SCS_auto, Loc,
4204  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4205  isStorageClass = true;
4206  break;
4207  case tok::kw___auto_type:
4208  Diag(Tok, diag::ext_auto_type);
4209  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_auto_type, Loc, PrevSpec,
4210  DiagID, Policy);
4211  break;
4212  case tok::kw_register:
4213  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpec(Actions, DeclSpec::SCS_register, Loc,
4214  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4215  isStorageClass = true;
4216  break;
4217  case tok::kw_mutable:
4218  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpec(Actions, DeclSpec::SCS_mutable, Loc,
4219  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4220  isStorageClass = true;
4221  break;
4222  case tok::kw___thread:
4223  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpecThread(DeclSpec::TSCS___thread, Loc,
4224  PrevSpec, DiagID);
4225  isStorageClass = true;
4226  break;
4227  case tok::kw_thread_local:
4228  if (getLangOpts().C23)
4229  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_c23_compat_keyword) << Tok.getName();
4230  // We map thread_local to _Thread_local in C23 mode so it retains the C
4231  // semantics rather than getting the C++ semantics.
4232  // FIXME: diagnostics will show _Thread_local when the user wrote
4233  // thread_local in source in C23 mode; we need some general way to
4234  // identify which way the user spelled the keyword in source.
4235  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpecThread(
4236  getLangOpts().C23 ? DeclSpec::TSCS__Thread_local
4237  : DeclSpec::TSCS_thread_local,
4238  Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4239  isStorageClass = true;
4240  break;
4241  case tok::kw__Thread_local:
4242  diagnoseUseOfC11Keyword(Tok);
4243  isInvalid = DS.SetStorageClassSpecThread(DeclSpec::TSCS__Thread_local,
4244  Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4245  isStorageClass = true;
4246  break;
4247 
4248  // function-specifier
4249  case tok::kw_inline:
4250  isInvalid = DS.setFunctionSpecInline(Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4251  break;
4252  case tok::kw_virtual:
4253  // C++ for OpenCL does not allow virtual function qualifier, to avoid
4254  // function pointers restricted in OpenCL v2.0 s6.9.a.
4255  if (getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus &&
4256  !getActions().getOpenCLOptions().isAvailableOption(
4257  "__cl_clang_function_pointers", getLangOpts())) {
4258  DiagID = diag::err_openclcxx_virtual_function;
4259  PrevSpec = Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getNameStart();
4260  isInvalid = true;
4261  } else {
4262  isInvalid = DS.setFunctionSpecVirtual(Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4263  }
4264  break;
4265  case tok::kw_explicit: {
4266  SourceLocation ExplicitLoc = Loc;
4267  SourceLocation CloseParenLoc;
4268  ExplicitSpecifier ExplicitSpec(nullptr, ExplicitSpecKind::ResolvedTrue);
4269  ConsumedEnd = ExplicitLoc;
4270  ConsumeToken(); // kw_explicit
4271  if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
4272  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 || isExplicitBool() == TPResult::True) {
4273  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20
4274  ? diag::warn_cxx17_compat_explicit_bool
4275  : diag::ext_explicit_bool);
4276 
4277  ExprResult ExplicitExpr(static_cast<Expr *>(nullptr));
4278  BalancedDelimiterTracker Tracker(*this, tok::l_paren);
4279  Tracker.consumeOpen();
4280 
4281  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext ConstantEvaluated(
4282  Actions, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
4283 
4284  ExplicitExpr = ParseConstantExpressionInExprEvalContext();
4285  ConsumedEnd = Tok.getLocation();
4286  if (ExplicitExpr.isUsable()) {
4287  CloseParenLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4288  Tracker.consumeClose();
4289  ExplicitSpec =
4290  Actions.ActOnExplicitBoolSpecifier(ExplicitExpr.get());
4291  } else
4292  Tracker.skipToEnd();
4293  } else {
4294  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::warn_cxx20_compat_explicit_bool);
4295  }
4296  }
4297  isInvalid = DS.setFunctionSpecExplicit(ExplicitLoc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4298  ExplicitSpec, CloseParenLoc);
4299  break;
4300  }
4301  case tok::kw__Noreturn:
4302  diagnoseUseOfC11Keyword(Tok);
4303  isInvalid = DS.setFunctionSpecNoreturn(Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4304  break;
4305 
4306  // friend
4307  case tok::kw_friend:
4308  if (DSContext == DeclSpecContext::DSC_class)
4309  isInvalid = DS.SetFriendSpec(Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4310  else {
4311  PrevSpec = ""; // not actually used by the diagnostic
4312  DiagID = diag::err_friend_invalid_in_context;
4313  isInvalid = true;
4314  }
4315  break;
4316 
4317  // Modules
4318  case tok::kw___module_private__:
4319  isInvalid = DS.setModulePrivateSpec(Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4320  break;
4321 
4322  // constexpr, consteval, constinit specifiers
4323  case tok::kw_constexpr:
4324  if (getLangOpts().C23)
4325  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_c23_compat_keyword) << Tok.getName();
4326  isInvalid = DS.SetConstexprSpec(ConstexprSpecKind::Constexpr, Loc,
4327  PrevSpec, DiagID);
4328  break;
4329  case tok::kw_consteval:
4330  isInvalid = DS.SetConstexprSpec(ConstexprSpecKind::Consteval, Loc,
4331  PrevSpec, DiagID);
4332  break;
4333  case tok::kw_constinit:
4334  isInvalid = DS.SetConstexprSpec(ConstexprSpecKind::Constinit, Loc,
4335  PrevSpec, DiagID);
4336  break;
4337 
4338  // type-specifier
4339  case tok::kw_short:
4340  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecWidth(TypeSpecifierWidth::Short, Loc, PrevSpec,
4341  DiagID, Policy);
4342  break;
4343  case tok::kw_long:
4344  if (DS.getTypeSpecWidth() != TypeSpecifierWidth::Long)
4345  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecWidth(TypeSpecifierWidth::Long, Loc, PrevSpec,
4346  DiagID, Policy);
4347  else
4348  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecWidth(TypeSpecifierWidth::LongLong, Loc,
4349  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4350  break;
4351  case tok::kw___int64:
4352  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecWidth(TypeSpecifierWidth::LongLong, Loc,
4353  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4354  break;
4355  case tok::kw_signed:
4356  isInvalid =
4357  DS.SetTypeSpecSign(TypeSpecifierSign::Signed, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4358  break;
4359  case tok::kw_unsigned:
4360  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecSign(TypeSpecifierSign::Unsigned, Loc, PrevSpec,
4361  DiagID);
4362  break;
4363  case tok::kw__Complex:
4364  if (!getLangOpts().C99)
4365  Diag(Tok, diag::ext_c99_feature) << Tok.getName();
4366  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecComplex(DeclSpec::TSC_complex, Loc, PrevSpec,
4367  DiagID);
4368  break;
4369  case tok::kw__Imaginary:
4370  if (!getLangOpts().C99)
4371  Diag(Tok, diag::ext_c99_feature) << Tok.getName();
4372  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecComplex(DeclSpec::TSC_imaginary, Loc, PrevSpec,
4373  DiagID);
4374  break;
4375  case tok::kw_void:
4376  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_void, Loc, PrevSpec,
4377  DiagID, Policy);
4378  break;
4379  case tok::kw_char:
4380  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_char, Loc, PrevSpec,
4381  DiagID, Policy);
4382  break;
4383  case tok::kw_int:
4384  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_int, Loc, PrevSpec,
4385  DiagID, Policy);
4386  break;
4387  case tok::kw__ExtInt:
4388  case tok::kw__BitInt: {
4389  DiagnoseBitIntUse(Tok);
4390  ExprResult ER = ParseExtIntegerArgument();
4391  if (ER.isInvalid())
4392  continue;
4393  isInvalid = DS.SetBitIntType(Loc, ER.get(), PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4394  ConsumedEnd = PrevTokLocation;
4395  break;
4396  }
4397  case tok::kw___int128:
4398  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_int128, Loc, PrevSpec,
4399  DiagID, Policy);
4400  break;
4401  case tok::kw_half:
4402  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_half, Loc, PrevSpec,
4403  DiagID, Policy);
4404  break;
4405  case tok::kw___bf16:
4406  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_BFloat16, Loc, PrevSpec,
4407  DiagID, Policy);
4408  break;
4409  case tok::kw_float:
4410  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_float, Loc, PrevSpec,
4411  DiagID, Policy);
4412  break;
4413  case tok::kw_double:
4414  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_double, Loc, PrevSpec,
4415  DiagID, Policy);
4416  break;
4417  case tok::kw__Float16:
4418  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_float16, Loc, PrevSpec,
4419  DiagID, Policy);
4420  break;
4421  case tok::kw__Accum:
4422  assert(getLangOpts().FixedPoint &&
4423  "This keyword is only used when fixed point types are enabled "
4424  "with `-ffixed-point`");
4425  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_accum, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4426  Policy);
4427  break;
4428  case tok::kw__Fract:
4429  assert(getLangOpts().FixedPoint &&
4430  "This keyword is only used when fixed point types are enabled "
4431  "with `-ffixed-point`");
4432  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_fract, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4433  Policy);
4434  break;
4435  case tok::kw__Sat:
4436  assert(getLangOpts().FixedPoint &&
4437  "This keyword is only used when fixed point types are enabled "
4438  "with `-ffixed-point`");
4439  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecSat(Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID);
4440  break;
4441  case tok::kw___float128:
4442  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_float128, Loc, PrevSpec,
4443  DiagID, Policy);
4444  break;
4445  case tok::kw___ibm128:
4446  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_ibm128, Loc, PrevSpec,
4447  DiagID, Policy);
4448  break;
4449  case tok::kw_wchar_t:
4450  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_wchar, Loc, PrevSpec,
4451  DiagID, Policy);
4452  break;
4453  case tok::kw_char8_t:
4454  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_char8, Loc, PrevSpec,
4455  DiagID, Policy);
4456  break;
4457  case tok::kw_char16_t:
4458  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_char16, Loc, PrevSpec,
4459  DiagID, Policy);
4460  break;
4461  case tok::kw_char32_t:
4462  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_char32, Loc, PrevSpec,
4463  DiagID, Policy);
4464  break;
4465  case tok::kw_bool:
4466  if (getLangOpts().C23)
4467  Diag(Tok, diag::warn_c23_compat_keyword) << Tok.getName();
4468  [[fallthrough]];
4469  case tok::kw__Bool:
4470  if (Tok.is(tok::kw__Bool) && !getLangOpts().C99)
4471  Diag(Tok, diag::ext_c99_feature) << Tok.getName();
4472 
4473  if (Tok.is(tok::kw_bool) &&
4474  DS.getTypeSpecType() != DeclSpec::TST_unspecified &&
4475  DS.getStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::SCS_typedef) {
4476  PrevSpec = ""; // Not used by the diagnostic.
4477  DiagID = diag::err_bool_redeclaration;
4478  // For better error recovery.
4479  Tok.setKind(tok::identifier);
4480  isInvalid = true;
4481  } else {
4482  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_bool, Loc, PrevSpec,
4483  DiagID, Policy);
4484  }
4485  break;
4486  case tok::kw__Decimal32:
4487  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_decimal32, Loc, PrevSpec,
4488  DiagID, Policy);
4489  break;
4490  case tok::kw__Decimal64:
4491  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_decimal64, Loc, PrevSpec,
4492  DiagID, Policy);
4493  break;
4494  case tok::kw__Decimal128:
4495  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_decimal128, Loc, PrevSpec,
4496  DiagID, Policy);
4497  break;
4498  case tok::kw___vector:
4499  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeAltiVecVector(true, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4500  break;
4501  case tok::kw___pixel:
4502  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeAltiVecPixel(true, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4503  break;
4504  case tok::kw___bool:
4505  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeAltiVecBool(true, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4506  break;
4507  case tok::kw_pipe:
4508  if (!getLangOpts().OpenCL ||
4509  getLangOpts().getOpenCLCompatibleVersion() < 200) {
4510  // OpenCL 2.0 and later define this keyword. OpenCL 1.2 and earlier
4511  // should support the "pipe" word as identifier.
4512  Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->revertTokenIDToIdentifier();
4513  Tok.setKind(tok::identifier);
4514  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
4515  } else if (!getLangOpts().OpenCLPipes) {
4516  DiagID = diag::err_opencl_unknown_type_specifier;
4517  PrevSpec = Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getNameStart();
4518  isInvalid = true;
4519  } else
4520  isInvalid = DS.SetTypePipe(true, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4521  break;
4522 // We only need to enumerate each image type once.
4523 #define IMAGE_READ_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
4524 #define IMAGE_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
4525 #define IMAGE_READ_TYPE(ImgType, Id, Ext) \
4526  case tok::kw_##ImgType##_t: \
4527  if (!handleOpenCLImageKW(Ext, DeclSpec::TST_##ImgType##_t)) \
4528  goto DoneWithDeclSpec; \
4529  break;
4530 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
4531  case tok::kw___unknown_anytype:
4532  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeSpecType(TST_unknown_anytype, Loc,
4533  PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
4534  break;
4535 
4536  // class-specifier:
4537  case tok::kw_class:
4538  case tok::kw_struct:
4539  case tok::kw___interface:
4540  case tok::kw_union: {
4541  tok::TokenKind Kind = Tok.getKind();
4542  ConsumeToken();
4543 
4544  // These are attributes following class specifiers.
4545  // To produce better diagnostic, we parse them when
4546  // parsing class specifier.
4547  ParsedAttributes Attributes(AttrFactory);
4548  ParseClassSpecifier(Kind, Loc, DS, TemplateInfo, AS,
4549  EnteringContext, DSContext, Attributes);
4550 
4551  // If there are attributes following class specifier,
4552  // take them over and handle them here.
4553  if (!Attributes.empty()) {
4554  AttrsLastTime = true;
4555  attrs.takeAllFrom(Attributes);
4556  }
4557  continue;
4558  }
4559 
4560  // enum-specifier:
4561  case tok::kw_enum:
4562  ConsumeToken();
4563  ParseEnumSpecifier(Loc, DS, TemplateInfo, AS, DSContext);
4564  continue;
4565 
4566  // cv-qualifier:
4567  case tok::kw_const:
4568  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_const, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4569  getLangOpts());
4570  break;
4571  case tok::kw_volatile:
4572  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_volatile, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4573  getLangOpts());
4574  break;
4575  case tok::kw_restrict:
4576  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_restrict, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4577  getLangOpts());
4578  break;
4579 
4580  // C++ typename-specifier:
4581  case tok::kw_typename:
4582  if (TryAnnotateTypeOrScopeToken()) {
4583  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
4584  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
4585  }
4586  if (!Tok.is(tok::kw_typename))
4587  continue;
4588  break;
4589 
4590  // C23/GNU typeof support.
4591  case tok::kw_typeof:
4592  case tok::kw_typeof_unqual:
4593  ParseTypeofSpecifier(DS);
4594  continue;
4595 
4596  case tok::annot_decltype:
4597  ParseDecltypeSpecifier(DS);
4598  continue;
4599 
4600  case tok::annot_pack_indexing_type:
4601  ParsePackIndexingType(DS);
4602  continue;
4603 
4604  case tok::annot_pragma_pack:
4605  HandlePragmaPack();
4606  continue;
4607 
4608  case tok::annot_pragma_ms_pragma:
4609  HandlePragmaMSPragma();
4610  continue;
4611 
4612  case tok::annot_pragma_ms_vtordisp:
4613  HandlePragmaMSVtorDisp();
4614  continue;
4615 
4616  case tok::annot_pragma_ms_pointers_to_members:
4617  HandlePragmaMSPointersToMembers();
4618  continue;
4619 
4620 #define TRANSFORM_TYPE_TRAIT_DEF(_, Trait) case tok::kw___##Trait:
4621 #include "clang/Basic/TransformTypeTraits.def"
4622  // HACK: libstdc++ already uses '__remove_cv' as an alias template so we
4623  // work around this by expecting all transform type traits to be suffixed
4624  // with '('. They're an identifier otherwise.
4625  if (!MaybeParseTypeTransformTypeSpecifier(DS))
4626  goto ParseIdentifier;
4627  continue;
4628 
4629  case tok::kw__Atomic:
4630  // C11 6.7.2.4/4:
4631  // If the _Atomic keyword is immediately followed by a left parenthesis,
4632  // it is interpreted as a type specifier (with a type name), not as a
4633  // type qualifier.
4634  diagnoseUseOfC11Keyword(Tok);
4635  if (NextToken().is(tok::l_paren)) {
4636  ParseAtomicSpecifier(DS);
4637  continue;
4638  }
4639  isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_atomic, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
4640  getLangOpts());
4641  break;
4642 
4643  // OpenCL address space qualifiers:
4644  case tok::kw___generic:
4645  // generic address space is introduced only in OpenCL v2.0
4646  // see OpenCL C Spec v2.0 s6.5.5
4647  // OpenCL v3.0 introduces __opencl_c_generic_address_space
4648  // feature macro to indicate if generic address space is supported
4649  if (!Actions.getLangOpts().OpenCLGenericAddressSpace) {
4650  DiagID = diag::err_opencl_unknown_type_specifier;
4651  PrevSpec = Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->getNameStart();
4652  isInvalid = true;
4653  break;
4654  }
4655  [[fallthrough]];
4656  case tok::kw_private:
4657  // It's fine (but redundant) to check this for __generic on the
4658  // fallthrough path; we only form the __generic token in OpenCL mode.
4659  if (!getLangOpts().OpenCL)
4660  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
4661  [[fallthrough]];
4662  case tok::kw___private:
4663  case tok::kw___global:
4664  case tok::kw___local:
4665  case tok::kw___constant:
4666  // OpenCL access qualifiers:
4667  case tok::kw___read_only:
4668  case tok::kw___write_only:
4669  case tok::kw___read_write:
4670  ParseOpenCLQualifiers(DS.getAttributes());
4671  break;
4672 
4673  case tok::kw_groupshared:
4674  case tok::kw_in:
4675  case tok::kw_inout:
4676  case tok::kw_out:
4677  // NOTE: ParseHLSLQualifiers will consume the qualifier token.
4678  ParseHLSLQualifiers(DS.getAttributes());
4679  continue;
4680 
4681  case tok::less:
4682  // GCC ObjC supports types like "<SomeProtocol>" as a synonym for
4683  // "id<SomeProtocol>". This is hopelessly old fashioned and dangerous,
4684  // but we support it.
4685  if (DS.hasTypeSpecifier() || !getLangOpts().ObjC)
4686  goto DoneWithDeclSpec;
4687 
4688  SourceLocation StartLoc = Tok.getLocation();
4689  SourceLocation EndLoc;
4690  TypeResult Type = parseObjCProtocolQualifierType(EndLoc);
4691  if (Type.isUsable()) {
4692  if (DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_typename, StartLoc, StartLoc,
4693  PrevSpec, DiagID, Type.get(),
4694  Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy()))
4695  Diag(StartLoc, DiagID) << PrevSpec;
4696 
4697  DS.SetRangeEnd(EndLoc);
4698  } else {
4699  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
4700  }
4701 
4702  // Need to support trailing type qualifiers (e.g. "id<p> const").
4703  // If a type specifier follows, it will be diagnosed elsewhere.
4704  continue;
4705  }
4706 
4707  DS.SetRangeEnd(ConsumedEnd.isValid() ? ConsumedEnd : Tok.getLocation());
4708 
4709  // If the specifier wasn't legal, issue a diagnostic.
4710  if (isInvalid) {
4711  assert(PrevSpec && "Method did not return previous specifier!");
4712  assert(DiagID);
4713 
4714  if (DiagID == diag::ext_duplicate_declspec ||
4715  DiagID == diag::ext_warn_duplicate_declspec ||
4716  DiagID == diag::err_duplicate_declspec)
4717  Diag(Loc, DiagID) << PrevSpec
4718  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(
4719  SourceRange(Loc, DS.getEndLoc()));
4720  else if (DiagID == diag::err_opencl_unknown_type_specifier) {
4721  Diag(Loc, DiagID) << getLangOpts().getOpenCLVersionString() << PrevSpec
4722  << isStorageClass;
4723  } else
4724  Diag(Loc, DiagID) << PrevSpec;
4725  }
4726 
4727  if (DiagID != diag::err_bool_redeclaration && ConsumedEnd.isInvalid())
4728  // After an error the next token can be an annotation token.
4729  ConsumeAnyToken();
4730 
4731  AttrsLastTime = false;
4732  }
4733 }
4734 
4735 static void DiagnoseCountAttributedTypeInUnnamedAnon(ParsingDeclSpec &DS,
4736  Parser &P) {
4737 
4738  if (DS.getTypeSpecType() != DeclSpec::TST_struct)
4739  return;
4740 
4741  auto *RD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(DS.getRepAsDecl());
4742  // We're only interested in unnamed, non-anonymous struct
4743  if (!RD || !RD->getName().empty() || RD->isAnonymousStructOrUnion())
4744  return;
4745 
4746  for (auto *I : RD->decls()) {
4747  auto *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(I);
4748  if (!VD)
4749  continue;
4750 
4751  auto *CAT = VD->getType()->getAs<CountAttributedType>();
4752  if (!CAT)
4753  continue;
4754 
4755  for (const auto &DD : CAT->dependent_decls()) {
4756  if (!RD->containsDecl(DD.getDecl())) {
4757  P.Diag(VD->getBeginLoc(),
4758  diag::err_flexible_array_count_not_in_same_struct)
4759  << DD.getDecl();
4760  P.Diag(DD.getDecl()->getBeginLoc(),
4761  diag::note_flexible_array_counted_by_attr_field)
4762  << DD.getDecl();
4763  }
4764  }
4765  }
4766 }
4767 
4768 /// ParseStructDeclaration - Parse a struct declaration without the terminating
4769 /// semicolon.
4770 ///
4771 /// Note that a struct declaration refers to a declaration in a struct,
4772 /// not to the declaration of a struct.
4773 ///
4774 /// struct-declaration:
4775 /// [C23] attributes-specifier-seq[opt]
4776 /// specifier-qualifier-list struct-declarator-list
4777 /// [GNU] __extension__ struct-declaration
4778 /// [GNU] specifier-qualifier-list
4779 /// struct-declarator-list:
4780 /// struct-declarator
4781 /// struct-declarator-list ',' struct-declarator
4782 /// [GNU] struct-declarator-list ',' attributes[opt] struct-declarator
4783 /// struct-declarator:
4784 /// declarator
4785 /// [GNU] declarator attributes[opt]
4786 /// declarator[opt] ':' constant-expression
4787 /// [GNU] declarator[opt] ':' constant-expression attributes[opt]
4788 ///
4789 void Parser::ParseStructDeclaration(
4790  ParsingDeclSpec &DS,
4791  llvm::function_ref<void(ParsingFieldDeclarator &)> FieldsCallback) {
4792 
4793  if (Tok.is(tok::kw___extension__)) {
4794  // __extension__ silences extension warnings in the subexpression.
4795  ExtensionRAIIObject O(Diags); // Use RAII to do this.
4796  ConsumeToken();
4797  return ParseStructDeclaration(DS, FieldsCallback);
4798  }
4799 
4800  // Parse leading attributes.
4801  ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
4802  MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(Attrs);
4803 
4804  // Parse the common specifier-qualifiers-list piece.
4805  ParseSpecifierQualifierList(DS);
4806 
4807  // If there are no declarators, this is a free-standing declaration
4808  // specifier. Let the actions module cope with it.
4809  if (Tok.is(tok::semi)) {
4810  // C23 6.7.2.1p9 : "The optional attribute specifier sequence in a
4811  // member declaration appertains to each of the members declared by the
4812  // member declarator list; it shall not appear if the optional member
4813  // declarator list is omitted."
4814  ProhibitAttributes(Attrs);
4815  RecordDecl *AnonRecord = nullptr;
4816  Decl *TheDecl = Actions.ParsedFreeStandingDeclSpec(
4817  getCurScope(), AS_none, DS, ParsedAttributesView::none(), AnonRecord);
4818  assert(!AnonRecord && "Did not expect anonymous struct or union here");
4819  DS.complete(TheDecl);
4820  return;
4821  }
4822 
4823  // Read struct-declarators until we find the semicolon.
4824  bool FirstDeclarator = true;
4825  SourceLocation CommaLoc;
4826  while (true) {
4827  ParsingFieldDeclarator DeclaratorInfo(*this, DS, Attrs);
4828  DeclaratorInfo.D.setCommaLoc(CommaLoc);
4829 
4830  // Attributes are only allowed here on successive declarators.
4831  if (!FirstDeclarator) {
4832  // However, this does not apply for [[]] attributes (which could show up
4833  // before or after the __attribute__ attributes).
4834  DiagnoseAndSkipCXX11Attributes();
4835  MaybeParseGNUAttributes(DeclaratorInfo.D);
4836  DiagnoseAndSkipCXX11Attributes();
4837  }
4838 
4839  /// struct-declarator: declarator
4840  /// struct-declarator: declarator[opt] ':' constant-expression
4841  if (Tok.isNot(tok::colon)) {
4842  // Don't parse FOO:BAR as if it were a typo for FOO::BAR.
4843  ColonProtectionRAIIObject X(*this);
4844  ParseDeclarator(DeclaratorInfo.D);
4845  } else
4846  DeclaratorInfo.D.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
4847 
4848  // Here, we now know that the unnamed struct is not an anonymous struct.
4849  // Report an error if a counted_by attribute refers to a field in a
4850  // different named struct.
4851  DiagnoseCountAttributedTypeInUnnamedAnon(DS, *this);
4852 
4853  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::colon)) {
4854  ExprResult Res(ParseConstantExpression());
4855  if (Res.isInvalid())
4856  SkipUntil(tok::semi, StopBeforeMatch);
4857  else
4858  DeclaratorInfo.BitfieldSize = Res.get();
4859  }
4860 
4861  // If attributes exist after the declarator, parse them.
4862  MaybeParseGNUAttributes(DeclaratorInfo.D);
4863 
4864  // We're done with this declarator; invoke the callback.
4865  FieldsCallback(DeclaratorInfo);
4866 
4867  // If we don't have a comma, it is either the end of the list (a ';')
4868  // or an error, bail out.
4869  if (!TryConsumeToken(tok::comma, CommaLoc))
4870  return;
4871 
4872  FirstDeclarator = false;
4873  }
4874 }
4875 
4876 /// ParseStructUnionBody
4877 /// struct-contents:
4878 /// struct-declaration-list
4879 /// [EXT] empty
4880 /// [GNU] "struct-declaration-list" without terminating ';'
4881 /// struct-declaration-list:
4882 /// struct-declaration
4883 /// struct-declaration-list struct-declaration
4884 /// [OBC] '@' 'defs' '(' class-name ')'
4885 ///
4886 void Parser::ParseStructUnionBody(SourceLocation RecordLoc,
4887  DeclSpec::TST TagType, RecordDecl *TagDecl) {
4888  PrettyDeclStackTraceEntry CrashInfo(Actions.Context, TagDecl, RecordLoc,
4889  "parsing struct/union body");
4890  assert(!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && "C++ declarations not supported");
4891 
4892  BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_brace);
4893  if (T.consumeOpen())
4894  return;
4895 
4896  ParseScope StructScope(this, Scope::ClassScope|Scope::DeclScope);
4897  Actions.ActOnTagStartDefinition(getCurScope(), TagDecl);
4898 
4899  // While we still have something to read, read the declarations in the struct.
4900  while (!tryParseMisplacedModuleImport() && Tok.isNot(tok::r_brace) &&
4901  Tok.isNot(tok::eof)) {
4902  // Each iteration of this loop reads one struct-declaration.
4903 
4904  // Check for extraneous top-level semicolon.
4905  if (Tok.is(tok::semi)) {
4906  ConsumeExtraSemi(InsideStruct, TagType);
4907  continue;
4908  }
4909 
4910  // Parse _Static_assert declaration.
4911  if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw__Static_assert, tok::kw_static_assert)) {
4912  SourceLocation DeclEnd;
4913  ParseStaticAssertDeclaration(DeclEnd);
4914  continue;
4915  }
4916 
4917  if (Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_pack)) {
4918  HandlePragmaPack();
4919  continue;
4920  }
4921 
4922  if (Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_align)) {
4923  HandlePragmaAlign();
4924  continue;
4925  }
4926 
4927  if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::annot_pragma_openmp, tok::annot_attr_openmp)) {
4928  // Result can be ignored, because it must be always empty.
4929  AccessSpecifier AS = AS_none;
4930  ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
4931  (void)ParseOpenMPDeclarativeDirectiveWithExtDecl(AS, Attrs);
4932  continue;
4933  }
4934 
4935  if (Tok.is(tok::annot_pragma_openacc)) {
4936  ParseOpenACCDirectiveDecl();
4937  continue;
4938  }
4939 
4940  if (tok::isPragmaAnnotation(Tok.getKind())) {
4941  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_pragma_misplaced_in_decl)
4942  << DeclSpec::getSpecifierName(
4943  TagType, Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy());
4944  ConsumeAnnotationToken();
4945  continue;
4946  }
4947 
4948  if (!Tok.is(tok::at)) {
4949  auto CFieldCallback = [&](ParsingFieldDeclarator &FD) {
4950  // Install the declarator into the current TagDecl.
4951  Decl *Field =
4952  Actions.ActOnField(getCurScope(), TagDecl,
4953  FD.D.getDeclSpec().getSourceRange().getBegin(),
4954  FD.D, FD.BitfieldSize);
4955  FD.complete(Field);
4956  };
4957 
4958  // Parse all the comma separated declarators.
4959  ParsingDeclSpec DS(*this);
4960  ParseStructDeclaration(DS, CFieldCallback);
4961  } else { // Handle @defs
4962  ConsumeToken();
4963  if (!Tok.isObjCAtKeyword(tok::objc_defs)) {
4964  Diag(Tok, diag::err_unexpected_at);
4965  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
4966  continue;
4967  }
4968  ConsumeToken();
4969  ExpectAndConsume(tok::l_paren);
4970  if (!Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
4971  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::identifier;
4972  SkipUntil(tok::semi);
4973  continue;
4974  }
4975  SmallVector<Decl *, 16> Fields;
4976  Actions.ActOnDefs(getCurScope(), TagDecl, Tok.getLocation(),
4977  Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), Fields);
4978  ConsumeToken();
4979  ExpectAndConsume(tok::r_paren);
4980  }
4981 
4982  if (TryConsumeToken(tok::semi))
4983  continue;
4984 
4985  if (Tok.is(tok::r_brace)) {
4986  ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::ext_expected_semi_decl_list);
4987  break;
4988  }
4989 
4990  ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::err_expected_semi_decl_list);
4991  // Skip to end of block or statement to avoid ext-warning on extra ';'.
4992  SkipUntil(tok::r_brace, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
4993  // If we stopped at a ';', eat it.
4994  TryConsumeToken(tok::semi);
4995  }
4996 
4997  T.consumeClose();
4998 
4999  ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
5000  // If attributes exist after struct contents, parse them.
5001  MaybeParseGNUAttributes(attrs);
5002 
5003  SmallVector<Decl *, 32> FieldDecls(TagDecl->fields());
5004 
5005  Actions.ActOnFields(getCurScope(), RecordLoc, TagDecl, FieldDecls,
5006  T.getOpenLocation(), T.getCloseLocation(), attrs);
5007  StructScope.Exit();
5008  Actions.ActOnTagFinishDefinition(getCurScope(), TagDecl, T.getRange());
5009 }
5010 
5011 /// ParseEnumSpecifier
5012 /// enum-specifier: [C99 6.7.2.2]
5013 /// 'enum' identifier[opt] '{' enumerator-list '}'
5014 ///[C99/C++]'enum' identifier[opt] '{' enumerator-list ',' '}'
5015 /// [GNU] 'enum' attributes[opt] identifier[opt] '{' enumerator-list ',' [opt]
5016 /// '}' attributes[opt]
5017 /// [MS] 'enum' __declspec[opt] identifier[opt] '{' enumerator-list ',' [opt]
5018 /// '}'
5019 /// 'enum' identifier
5020 /// [GNU] 'enum' attributes[opt] identifier
5021 ///
5022 /// [C++11] enum-head '{' enumerator-list[opt] '}'
5023 /// [C++11] enum-head '{' enumerator-list ',' '}'
5024 ///
5025 /// enum-head: [C++11]
5026 /// enum-key attribute-specifier-seq[opt] identifier[opt] enum-base[opt]
5027 /// enum-key attribute-specifier-seq[opt] nested-name-specifier
5028 /// identifier enum-base[opt]
5029 ///
5030 /// enum-key: [C++11]
5031 /// 'enum'
5032 /// 'enum' 'class'
5033 /// 'enum' 'struct'
5034 ///
5035 /// enum-base: [C++11]
5036 /// ':' type-specifier-seq
5037 ///
5038 /// [C++] elaborated-type-specifier:
5039 /// [C++] 'enum' nested-name-specifier[opt] identifier
5040 ///
5041 void Parser::ParseEnumSpecifier(SourceLocation StartLoc, DeclSpec &DS,
5042  const ParsedTemplateInfo &TemplateInfo,
5043  AccessSpecifier AS, DeclSpecContext DSC) {
5044  // Parse the tag portion of this.
5045  if (Tok.is(tok::code_completion)) {
5046  // Code completion for an enum name.
5047  cutOffParsing();
5048  Actions.CodeCompleteTag(getCurScope(), DeclSpec::TST_enum);
5049  DS.SetTypeSpecError(); // Needed by ActOnUsingDeclaration.
5050  return;
5051  }
5052 
5053  // If attributes exist after tag, parse them.
5054  ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
5055  MaybeParseAttributes(PAKM_GNU | PAKM_Declspec | PAKM_CXX11, attrs);
5056 
5057  SourceLocation ScopedEnumKWLoc;
5058  bool IsScopedUsingClassTag = false;
5059 
5060  // In C++11, recognize 'enum class' and 'enum struct'.
5061  if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::kw_class, tok::kw_struct) && getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5062  Diag(Tok, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ? diag::warn_cxx98_compat_scoped_enum
5063  : diag::ext_scoped_enum);
5064  IsScopedUsingClassTag = Tok.is(tok::kw_class);
5065  ScopedEnumKWLoc = ConsumeToken();
5066 
5067  // Attributes are not allowed between these keywords. Diagnose,
5068  // but then just treat them like they appeared in the right place.
5069  ProhibitAttributes(attrs);
5070 
5071  // They are allowed afterwards, though.
5072  MaybeParseAttributes(PAKM_GNU | PAKM_Declspec | PAKM_CXX11, attrs);
5073  }
5074 
5075  // C++11 [temp.explicit]p12:
5076  // The usual access controls do not apply to names used to specify
5077  // explicit instantiations.
5078  // We extend this to also cover explicit specializations. Note that
5079  // we don't suppress if this turns out to be an elaborated type
5080  // specifier.
5081  bool shouldDelayDiagsInTag =
5082  (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitInstantiation ||
5083  TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitSpecialization);
5084  SuppressAccessChecks diagsFromTag(*this, shouldDelayDiagsInTag);
5085 
5086  // Determine whether this declaration is permitted to have an enum-base.
5087  AllowDefiningTypeSpec AllowEnumSpecifier =
5088  isDefiningTypeSpecifierContext(DSC, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus);
5089  bool CanBeOpaqueEnumDeclaration =
5090  DS.isEmpty() && isOpaqueEnumDeclarationContext(DSC);
5091  bool CanHaveEnumBase = (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 || getLangOpts().ObjC ||
5092  getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt) &&
5093  (AllowEnumSpecifier == AllowDefiningTypeSpec::Yes ||
5094  CanBeOpaqueEnumDeclaration);
5095 
5096  CXXScopeSpec &SS = DS.getTypeSpecScope();
5097  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5098  // "enum foo : bar;" is not a potential typo for "enum foo::bar;".
5099  ColonProtectionRAIIObject X(*this);
5100 
5101  CXXScopeSpec Spec;
5102  if (ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(Spec, /*ObjectType=*/nullptr,
5103  /*ObjectHasErrors=*/false,
5104  /*EnteringContext=*/true))
5105  return;
5106 
5107  if (Spec.isSet() && Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
5108  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::identifier;
5109  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
5110  if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_brace)) {
5111  // Has no name and is not a definition.
5112  // Skip the rest of this declarator, up until the comma or semicolon.
5113  SkipUntil(tok::comma, StopAtSemi);
5114  return;
5115  }
5116  }
5117 
5118  SS = Spec;
5119  }
5120 
5121  // Must have either 'enum name' or 'enum {...}' or (rarely) 'enum : T { ... }'.
5122  if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier) && Tok.isNot(tok::l_brace) &&
5123  Tok.isNot(tok::colon)) {
5124  Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_either) << tok::identifier << tok::l_brace;
5125 
5126  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
5127  // Skip the rest of this declarator, up until the comma or semicolon.
5128  SkipUntil(tok::comma, StopAtSemi);
5129  return;
5130  }
5131 
5132  // If an identifier is present, consume and remember it.
5133  IdentifierInfo *Name = nullptr;
5134  SourceLocation NameLoc;
5135  if (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
5136  Name = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
5137  NameLoc = ConsumeToken();
5138  }
5139 
5140  if (!Name && ScopedEnumKWLoc.isValid()) {
5141  // C++0x 7.2p2: The optional identifier shall not be omitted in the
5142  // declaration of a scoped enumeration.
5143  Diag(Tok, diag::err_scoped_enum_missing_identifier);
5144  ScopedEnumKWLoc = SourceLocation();
5145  IsScopedUsingClassTag = false;
5146  }
5147 
5148  // Okay, end the suppression area. We'll decide whether to emit the
5149  // diagnostics in a second.
5150  if (shouldDelayDiagsInTag)
5151  diagsFromTag.done();
5152 
5153  TypeResult BaseType;
5154  SourceRange BaseRange;
5155 
5156  bool CanBeBitfield =
5157  getCurScope()->isClassScope() && ScopedEnumKWLoc.isInvalid() && Name;
5158 
5159  // Parse the fixed underlying type.
5160  if (Tok.is(tok::colon)) {
5161  // This might be an enum-base or part of some unrelated enclosing context.
5162  //
5163  // 'enum E : base' is permitted in two circumstances:
5164  //
5165  // 1) As a defining-type-specifier, when followed by '{'.
5166  // 2) As the sole constituent of a complete declaration -- when DS is empty
5167  // and the next token is ';'.
5168  //
5169  // The restriction to defining-type-specifiers is important to allow parsing
5170  // a ? new enum E : int{}
5171  // _Generic(a, enum E : int{})
5172  // properly.
5173  //
5174  // One additional consideration applies:
5175  //
5176  // C++ [dcl.enum]p1:
5177  // A ':' following "enum nested-name-specifier[opt] identifier" within
5178  // the decl-specifier-seq of a member-declaration is parsed as part of
5179  // an enum-base.
5180  //
5181  // Other language modes supporting enumerations with fixed underlying types
5182  // do not have clear rules on this, so we disambiguate to determine whether
5183  // the tokens form a bit-field width or an enum-base.
5184 
5185  if (CanBeBitfield && !isEnumBase(CanBeOpaqueEnumDeclaration)) {
5186  // Outside C++11, do not interpret the tokens as an enum-base if they do
5187  // not make sense as one. In C++11, it's an error if this happens.
5188  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
5189  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_anonymous_enum_bitfield);
5190  } else if (CanHaveEnumBase || !ColonIsSacred) {
5191  SourceLocation ColonLoc = ConsumeToken();
5192 
5193  // Parse a type-specifier-seq as a type. We can't just ParseTypeName here,
5194  // because under -fms-extensions,
5195  // enum E : int *p;
5196  // declares 'enum E : int; E *p;' not 'enum E : int*; E p;'.
5197  DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
5198  // enum-base is not assumed to be a type and therefore requires the
5199  // typename keyword [p0634r3].
5200  ParseSpecifierQualifierList(DS, ImplicitTypenameContext::No, AS,
5201  DeclSpecContext::DSC_type_specifier);
5202  Declarator DeclaratorInfo(DS, ParsedAttributesView::none(),
5203  DeclaratorContext::TypeName);
5204  BaseType = Actions.ActOnTypeName(DeclaratorInfo);
5205 
5206  BaseRange = SourceRange(ColonLoc, DeclaratorInfo.getSourceRange().getEnd());
5207 
5208  if (!getLangOpts().ObjC && !getLangOpts().C23) {
5209  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
5210  Diag(ColonLoc, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_enum_fixed_underlying_type)
5211  << BaseRange;
5212  else if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
5213  Diag(ColonLoc, diag::ext_cxx11_enum_fixed_underlying_type)
5214  << BaseRange;
5215  else if (getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt)
5216  Diag(ColonLoc, diag::ext_ms_c_enum_fixed_underlying_type)
5217  << BaseRange;
5218  else
5219  Diag(ColonLoc, diag::ext_clang_c_enum_fixed_underlying_type)
5220  << BaseRange;
5221  }
5222  }
5223  }
5224 
5225  // There are four options here. If we have 'friend enum foo;' then this is a
5226  // friend declaration, and cannot have an accompanying definition. If we have
5227  // 'enum foo;', then this is a forward declaration. If we have
5228  // 'enum foo {...' then this is a definition. Otherwise we have something
5229  // like 'enum foo xyz', a reference.
5230  //
5231  // This is needed to handle stuff like this right (C99 6.7.2.3p11):
5232  // enum foo {..}; void bar() { enum foo; } <- new foo in bar.
5233  // enum foo {..}; void bar() { enum foo x; } <- use of old foo.
5234  //
5235  Sema::TagUseKind TUK;
5236  if (AllowEnumSpecifier == AllowDefiningTypeSpec::No)
5237  TUK = Sema::TUK_Reference;
5238  else if (Tok.is(tok::l_brace)) {
5239  if (DS.isFriendSpecified()) {
5240  Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_friend_decl_defines_type)
5241  << SourceRange(DS.getFriendSpecLoc());
5242  ConsumeBrace();
5243  SkipUntil(tok::r_brace, StopAtSemi);
5244  // Discard any other definition-only pieces.
5245  attrs.clear();
5246  ScopedEnumKWLoc = SourceLocation();
5247  IsScopedUsingClassTag = false;
5248  BaseType = TypeResult();
5249  TUK = Sema::TUK_Friend;
5250  } else {
5251  TUK = Sema::TUK_Definition;
5252  }
5253  } else if (!isTypeSpecifier(DSC) &&
5254  (Tok.is(tok::semi) ||
5255  (Tok.isAtStartOfLine() &&
5256  !isValidAfterTypeSpecifier(CanBeBitfield)))) {
5257  // An opaque-enum-declaration is required to be standalone (no preceding or
5258  // following tokens in the declaration). Sema enforces this separately by
5259  // diagnosing anything else in the DeclSpec.
5260  TUK = DS.isFriendSpecified() ? Sema::TUK_Friend : Sema::TUK_Declaration;
5261  if (Tok.isNot(tok::semi)) {
5262  // A semicolon was missing after this declaration. Diagnose and recover.
5263  ExpectAndConsume(tok::semi, diag::err_expected_after, "enum");
5264  PP.EnterToken(Tok, /*IsReinject=*/true);
5265  Tok.setKind(tok::semi);
5266  }
5267  } else {
5268  TUK = Sema::TUK_Reference;
5269  }
5270 
5271  bool IsElaboratedTypeSpecifier =
5272  TUK == Sema::TUK_Reference || TUK == Sema::TUK_Friend;
5273 
5274  // If this is an elaborated type specifier nested in a larger declaration,
5275  // and we delayed diagnostics before, just merge them into the current pool.
5276  if (TUK == Sema::TUK_Reference && shouldDelayDiagsInTag) {
5277  diagsFromTag.redelay();
5278  }
5279 
5280  MultiTemplateParamsArg TParams;
5281  if (TemplateInfo.Kind != ParsedTemplateInfo::NonTemplate &&
5282  TUK != Sema::TUK_Reference) {
5283  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 || !SS.isSet()) {
5284  // Skip the rest of this declarator, up until the comma or semicolon.
5285  Diag(Tok, diag::err_enum_template);
5286  SkipUntil(tok::comma, StopAtSemi);
5287  return;
5288  }
5289 
5290  if (TemplateInfo.Kind == ParsedTemplateInfo::ExplicitInstantiation) {
5291  // Enumerations can't be explicitly instantiated.
5292  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
5293  Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_explicit_instantiation_enum);
5294  return;
5295  }
5296 
5297  assert(TemplateInfo.TemplateParams && "no template parameters");
5298  TParams = MultiTemplateParamsArg(TemplateInfo.TemplateParams->data(),
5299  TemplateInfo.TemplateParams->size());
5300  SS.setTemplateParamLists(TParams);
5301  }
5302 
5303  if (!Name && TUK != Sema::TUK_Definition) {
5304  Diag(Tok, diag::err_enumerator_unnamed_no_def);
5305 
5306  DS.SetTypeSpecError();
5307  // Skip the rest of this declarator, up until the comma or semicolon.
5308  SkipUntil(tok::comma, StopAtSemi);
5309  return;
5310  }
5311 
5312  // An elaborated-type-specifier has a much more constrained grammar:
5313  //
5314  // 'enum' nested-name-specifier[opt] identifier
5315  //
5316  // If we parsed any other bits, reject them now.
5317  //
5318  // MSVC and (for now at least) Objective-C permit a full enum-specifier
5319  // or opaque-enum-declaration anywhere.
5320  if (IsElaboratedTypeSpecifier && !getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt &&
5321  !getLangOpts().ObjC) {
5322  ProhibitCXX11Attributes(attrs, diag::err_attributes_not_allowed,
5323  diag::err_keyword_not_allowed,
5324  /*DiagnoseEmptyAttrs=*/true);
5325  if (BaseType.isUsable())
5326  Diag(BaseRange.getBegin(), diag::ext_enum_base_in_type_specifier)
5327  << (AllowEnumSpecifier == AllowDefiningTypeSpec::Yes) << BaseRange;
5328  else if (ScopedEnumKWLoc.isValid())
5329  Diag(ScopedEnumKWLoc, diag::ext_elaborated_enum_class)
5330  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(ScopedEnumKWLoc) << IsScopedUsingClassTag;
5331  }
5332 
5333  stripTypeAttributesOffDeclSpec(attrs, DS, TUK);
5334 
5335  SkipBodyInfo SkipBody;
5336  if (!Name && TUK == Sema::TUK_Definition && Tok.is(tok::l_brace) &&
5337  NextToken().is(tok::identifier))
5338  SkipBody = Actions.shouldSkipAnonEnumBody(getCurScope(),
5339  NextToken().getIdentifierInfo(),
5340  NextToken().getLocation());
5341 
5342  bool Owned = false;
5343  bool IsDependent = false;
5344  const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
5345  unsigned DiagID;
5346  Decl *TagDecl =
5347  Actions.ActOnTag(getCurScope(), DeclSpec::TST_enum, TUK, StartLoc, SS,
5348  Name, NameLoc, attrs, AS, DS.getModulePrivateSpecLoc(),
